Example
Display an alert box:

Copy
alert("Hello! I am an alert box!!");

Description
The alert() method displays an alert box with a specified message and an OK button.

The alert box takes the focus away from the current window.

It forces the browser to read the message.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
alert()	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
alert(message)
Parameter Values
Parameter
Type
Description
message


String


Optional.
the text to display in the alert box, or
an object converted into a string and displayed
Return Value
No return value

More Examples
Alert box with line-breaks:

Copy
alert("Hello\nHow are you?");

Example
Alert the hostname of the current URL:

Copy
alert(location.hostname);
